results.title: A World Apart
results.description: The X-Men are on a mind bending romp to stop the Juggernaut who is on an interdimensional rampage; Professor X's astral form is trapped within Wolverine.

results.title: Yesterday's News
results.description: The X-Men are transported to the Skrull homeworld on the eve of its being devoured by Galactus.

results.title: The Not So Big Easy
results.description: The X-Men fight a Brood infected Ghost Rider beneath the streets of New Orleans and try to find a way to seperate him from the alien menace.

results.title: Eve of Destruction
results.description: Marrow is healed; Galactus eats the Skrull homeworld (again); The X-Men return to earth.

results.title: Technical Difficulties
results.description: The X-Men reunite at the Mansion; Kitty, Kurt and Peter follow the SHIELD ship that has captured Douglock to the Helicarrier; SHIELD is unprepared for the massive techno-organic virus Doug infects them with; The Red Skull is revealed as the one who is pulling Douglock's strings.

results.title: Dream's End Part 2: Pressure Points
results.description: Xavier's fits of rage and unstable nature cause the X-Men to disband for a much needed break.

results.title: Hidden Lives Part 1: Open Wounds
results.description: A number of mysterious baddies are gunning for Mystique and she turns to Rogue for help; Nightcrawler runs into Polaris at church and she tells him of her feeling that Havok is still alive (He apparently died in X-Factor #149).

results.title: Hidden Lives Part 2: Pandora's Box
results.description: Rogue and Sunfire help to clear Mystique's name with the Japanese authorities; Kitty finds Destiny's journals.

results.title: Test to Destruction
results.description: Professor X telepathically makes his X-Men fight some of their most dangerous foes to make sure they haven't lost their edge.

results.title: Do Unto Others
results.description: The X-Men invade the Skrull base to find the missing Wolverine; Wolvie himself shows up as Apocalypse's new Angel of Death.
